variables.name: NONE
variables.comment: WPA is not used; plaintext or static WEP could be used.

variables.name: WPA_PSK
variables.comment: WPA pre-shared key (requires {@code preSharedKey} to be specified).

variables.name: WPA_EAP
variables.comment: WPA using EAP authentication. Generally used with an external authentication server.

variables.name: IEEE8021X
variables.comment:
* IEEE 802.1X using EAP authentication and (optionally) dynamically
         * generated WEP keys.

variables.name: WPA2_PSK
variables.comment:
* WPA2 pre-shared key for use with soft access point
         * (requires {@code preSharedKey} to be specified).

variables.name: FT_PSK
variables.comment: * IEEE 802.11r Fast BSS Transition with PSK authentication.

variables.name: FT_EAP
variables.comment: * IEEE 802.11r Fast BSS Transition with EAP authentication.

variables.name: WPA_PSK_SHA256
variables.comment: * WPA pre-shared key with stronger SHA256-based algorithms.

variables.name: WPA_EAP_SHA256
variables.comment: * WPA using EAP authentication with stronger SHA256-based algorithms.

variables.name: WAPI_PSK
variables.comment: * WAPI pre-shared key (requires {@code preSharedKey} to be specified).

variables.name: DPP
variables.comment: * Easy Connect - AKA Device Provisioning Protocol (DPP) * For more details, visit https://www.wi-fi.org/ and * search for "Easy Connect" or "Device Provisioning Protocol specification".
